Retail Sales Data Pipeline - Day 1 Summary

Bootcamp Project 1

Objective

The objective of Day 1 was to understand the project requirements, create the GitHub repository structure, and design the end-to-end architecture for the Azure Data Engineering pipeline.

Activities Completed

* GitHub repository created
* Project folder structure created
* Architecture diagram designed using Draw.io
* Source systems finalized
* Medallion Architecture planned
* Initial documentation created


Source Systems Planned

REST API

* [https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/users](https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/users)
* [https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/posts](https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/posts)

SQL Tables

* customers
* products
* product_category
* orders
* sales

### CSV File

* inventory_updates.csv


Planned Architecture Flow

REST API / SQL / CSV
        ↓
Azure Data Factory Pipelines
        ↓
Bronze Layer (Raw CSV Files)
        ↓
ADF Data Flow Transformations
        ↓
Silver Layer (Cleaned Parquet Files)
        ↓
Gold Business Aggregations
        ↓
Azure SQL Reporting Tables
        ↓
Power BI Dashboard


## Key Learnings

* Understanding Medallion Architecture
* Difference between Bronze, Silver, and Gold layers
* Role of Azure Data Factory in orchestration
* Importance of architecture design in Data Engineering projects


